              "content": "# Pemberton RFQ — Indemnity & GTCs Exposure Analysis\n\n## Current Status\n- Analyzing GTCs (Doc 05) override on indemnities vs. MSA (Doc 02)\n- Mapping worst-case exposure if GTCs take precedence\n- Deadline: 19 June 2026 (24 days)\n\n## Key Finding\nGTCs contain MORE AGGRESSIVE indemnity language than MSA:\n- MSA Clause 10: Supplier indemnifies for breach, negligence, defect, IP, and \"any applicable law\" — UNCAPPED but listed heads\n- GTCs (Page 4): Supplier liability \"unlimited in respect of\" (i) death/PI, (ii) fraud, (iii) breach of confidentiality, (iv) Foreground IP infringement, (v) loss of tangible property at Buyer's site, (vi) Supplier's indemnity obligations\n- **GTCs precedence (Clause 20.1) = GTCs indemnity override MSA indemnity**\n\n## Questions to Resolve\n1. Does GTCs indemnity fully replace MSA indemnity or augment it?\n2. What is \"loss of tangible property at Buyer's site\" — does this cover Buyer's inventory damage?\n3. Is there a total cap on GTCs indemnity or is it fully unlimited?\n\n## Action Items\n- [ ] Map exact GTCs indemnity language vs. MSA\n- [ ] Quantify worst-case exposure on £18.4m/year spend\n- [ ] Determine if insurance will cover GTCs-level indemnity\n- [ ] Escalate to GC/Board if exposure exceeds risk appetite\n"
